description: LUBBOCK, Texas – The No. 5 Texas Tech baseball team's senior class was sent off the right way on Saturday, handing Oklahoma a 10-2 defeat at Rip Griffin Park on Senior Day in the Big 12 regular-season finale. The Red Raiders finished the regular season 36-18, 15-9 in Big 12 play and earned a 2-seed in the Big 12 tournament which begins Wednesday, May 25. Tech will face the 7-seed Kansas State at 4 p.m.
